      <h2 class="text-base font-semibold leading-7 text-indigo-600">Common Questions</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl">
        Understanding Voqua
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="mx-auto mt-16 max-w-2xl sm:mt-20 lg:mt-24 lg:max-w-4xl">
      <dl class="space-y-10">
        <div>
          <dt class="text-lg font-semibold leading-7 text-gray-900">
            How is Voqua different from regular surveys?
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-gray-600">
            Unlike traditional surveys where all votes carry equal weight, Voqua lets people show how strongly they feel about each option. This reveals the true priorities of your team and helps surface the most important insights.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="text-lg font-semibold leading-7 text-gray-900">
            What makes this better for decision making?
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-gray-600">
            This approach encourages people to think more carefully about their choices. This leads to more thoughtful responses and helps filter out casual opinions from deeply held convictions.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="text-lg font-semibold leading-7 text-gray-900">
            How does the voting system work?
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-gray-600">
            Each person gets a pool of voting credits. They can spread these across different options, or concentrate them to show strong support for specific choices. The more credits used on one option, the more it costs - encouraging balanced, thoughtful voting.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt class="text-lg font-semibold leading-7 text-gray-900">
            What kind of decisions is this best for?
          </dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-base leading-7 text-gray-600">
            Voqua excels at prioritizing features, gathering product feedback, making resource allocation decisions, and any situation where you need to understand what truly matters to your team or customers.
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

